      • initializeRandomGenerators

        private int initializeRandomGenerators()
        Several random generators are used in the model. Each is controlled by a seed and provides variability for specific features or processes in the model.
        Each random generator is controlled by a specific seed that can be fixed or changed. When fixed, the random generator always provides the same pseudorandom series of numbers.
        This makes it possible to carry out simulations in which only selected sources of variation change. author: J. Le Fur 2012, rev. 08.2014
        Returns:
        nbGen the number of random generators initialized at that time
